## Facilitation Notes

{% if difficulty == "Introductory" %}
- **Start with intuition** — use a real-world analogy before introducing formal methods
- **Pace for questions** — introductory audiences need more processing time
- **Pair activity** — have students discuss concepts in pairs before group share
{% elif difficulty == "Intermediate" %}
- **Build on prior modules** — reference tools and concepts from earlier phases
- **Use software live** — demonstrate in Minitab/JMP, then have students replicate
- **Check for understanding** — quick polls or show-of-hands after each major concept
{% else %}
- **Focus on decision-making** — emphasize when and why to use each tool, not just how
- **Challenge assumptions** — present edge cases and ask students to identify the approach
- **Connect to capstone** — have students map techniques directly to their capstone project
{% endif %}

## Common Issues and Resolutions

{% if difficulty == "Introductory" %}
| Issue | Resolution |
|-------|------------|
| Students overwhelmed by terminology | Provide a glossary handout; pause for questions after each new term |
| Software not installed | Use cloud-based Minitab Express or pre-configured RStudio Cloud |
| Exercises too slow | Provide partially completed templates for students to finish |

{% elif difficulty == "Intermediate" %}
| Issue | Resolution |
|-------|------------|
| Incorrect tool selection | Review the decision flowchart; use a "which tool when" reference card |
| Statistical assumptions violated | Teach assumption-checking procedures before each analysis |
| Results don't match expected | Have students verify data entry and check for outliers first |

{% else %}
| Issue | Resolution |
|-------|------------|
| Over-reliance on p-values | Emphasize practical significance and effect sizes alongside statistical tests |
| DOE designs too complex | Start with 2-factor full factorial, then build up to fractional designs |
| Capstone integration unclear | Provide a DMEDI deliverables checklist mapped to specific modules |

{% endif %}

